1
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,300
What do you need?

2
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:15,233
Gen. Ramirez had
me picked up last night.

3
00:00:15,367 --> 00:00:17,367
He asked about you two.

4
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:19,700
He had you investigated.

5
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,333
What? You sold us out?

6
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:24,900
No. I wouldn't rat out a
group I'm trying to join.

7
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:29,767
I'm just wondering why
Diaz's man shoot his son.

8
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,500
I'd understand if it was
Samuel's son they targeted.

9
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:35,233
Maybe he's also a scammer.

10
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,600
And he's in cahoots
with your lover.

11
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:40,333
Gen. Ramirez has
his eyes on Roldan,

12
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:43,467
but I'm not sure we
can trust him or his men.

13
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,433
Johnny's starting
to get suspicious.

14
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:49,200
Ever since the shooting
incident involving you and Enzo,

15
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:52,000
he's been asking around
about Oriental Ridge.

16
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:53,767
The important thing is,

17
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:58,500
this mission must stay
between the three of us.

18
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:03,700
You'll get nothing from me.
I won't tell you a thing.

19
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:06,333
Cocky, huh? But...

20
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:10,500
I've got a plan for Samuel.

21
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:16,467
This is something that will be
impossible for him to survive.

22
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:20,500
You know, Samuel,
this is a big amount.

23
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:22,833
That's already
half of what we lost.

24
00:01:22,967 --> 00:01:27,367
You might not have anything
left for you or your family.

25
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:29,000
That's fine.

26
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:33,700
My work bonus is pretty big too.

27
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:36,533
My father scammed
so many others.

28
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:41,467
Please help me find them,

29
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:44,033
so I can at least help them too.

30
00:01:44,167 --> 00:01:46,667
We'll take care of
tracking the other victims.

31
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,833
Thanks. But please...
keep this between us.

32
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:52,033
Sure.

33
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:54,633
I can't rush it.

34
00:01:54,767 --> 00:01:57,900
I'll return your
money little by little,

35
00:01:58,033 --> 00:02:00,067
so the plan won't blow up.

36
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:03,333
[PHONE RINGING]

37
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:05,767
Hello, Agnes?

38
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:07,600
Okay. Let's meet up.

39
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:17,333
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:37,233 --> 00:02:39,467
Oh, come on.
Don't worry about it.

41
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:41,567
This is part of the mission.

42
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,533
It's my duty to
protect you, especially

43
00:02:43,667 --> 00:02:47,200
since I convinced
you to let us help.

44
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:48,633
Thank you.

45
00:02:48,767 --> 00:02:53,100
You didn't have to stick
around, but here you are.

46
00:02:53,233 --> 00:02:55,667
Agnes, I really appreciate it.

47
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,700
Thank you.

48
00:02:58,467 --> 00:03:00,667
It's nothing. Besides,
I wanted to see King.

49
00:03:05,867 --> 00:03:07,000
- Oh!
- Dad!

50
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:08,867
- Son.
- Aunt Agnes!

51
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,767
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

52
00:03:13,233 --> 00:03:15,167
Oh, how are you, King?

53
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:18,433
Teacher gave me a star today!

54
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:21,000
And I made a new
friend at school.

55
00:03:21,167 --> 00:03:26,467
Wow! You study well and have
lots of friends. Very good!

56
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:29,900
What's your new friend's name?

57
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:31,267
Chloe.

58
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:34,167
Her mom picked her up earlier.

59
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:37,000
I hope you get to meet her too.

60
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:39,800
- Mm-hmm.
- I hope so.

61
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:40,800
Next time.

62
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,667
Oh. Oh.

63
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,033
- Mm?
- Okay. Okay.

64
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:48,100
[CHUCKLING SOFTLY]

65
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:54,433
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:57,067
- Good evening!
- Good evening.

67
00:03:58,567 --> 00:04:00,867
Ma. Arissa.

68
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:03,700
Son.

69
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:08,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES,
THEN FADES]

70
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:15,067
Roldan, you think Trinidad's
finally out of our way?

71
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,233
[LAUGHS SINISTERLY]

72
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:18,467
Jacob...

73
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:20,933
This is what we've
been waiting for.

74
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:27,033
That bastard Trinidad will
be out of our lives for good.

75
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,900
Get everything ready.

76
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:34,800
Done.

77
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,100
[GLASSES CLINK]

78
00:04:37,233 --> 00:04:43,033
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:45,300
[ROLDAN LAUGHING]

80
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:52,467
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

81
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,100
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

82
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:58,067
"Hi love, how are you?"

83
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:02,067
- Bro. Okay.
- Bro, we'll go now.

84
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:04,633
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

85
00:05:04,767 --> 00:05:08,733
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:11,933
"Just busy with work."

87
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:14,200
"Don't tire yourself out.
Rest too."

88
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:19,500
"Careful, you might
end up like Dad.

89
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:24,067
He got sick, and we're
drowning in hospital bills."

90
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:27,000
"How much?"

91
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:34,000
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:49,700
"50,000 pesos."

93
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,933
"That's huge.
I only have 15,000."

94
00:05:52,067 --> 00:05:59,033
- [GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [KEYBOARD CLACKING]

95
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:06,700
"That's fine, love. Any amount
helps Dad. Thank you! Mwah!"

96
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:12,900
"Okay,
I'll send it through Cash Zing."

97
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:20,033
- [GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [KEYBOARD CLACKING]

98
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,800
Hey...

99
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:27,133
- Nice one.
- Sir, I didn't see you there.

100
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:28,200
Your girlfriend?

101
00:06:29,867 --> 00:06:30,733
No.

102
00:06:30,867 --> 00:06:33,133
Come on, let me see.

103
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:34,833
Sir, don't.

104
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,733
She is your girlfriend.

105
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:38,233
Which club did you meet her at?

106
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:41,167
- Club?
- Oh, really?

107
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,633
- She's not that kind of girl.
- Let me see.

108
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:44,867
She's a good woman. Yeah.

109
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,933
You're just scared
I'll steal her.

110
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:50,433
Wow, sir, you already
have Delilah and Agnes.

111
00:06:50,567 --> 00:06:51,767
Let me have this one.

112
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,700
Anyway, say goodbye
to your girlfriend.

113
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,133
We've got a new assignment.

114
00:06:55,267 --> 00:06:56,333
Come on.

115
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,867
Huh? Sir, where?

116
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:00,533
[UTENSILS CLINKING]

117
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:03,600
Thank you so much for
the food, Ma'am Lolita.

118
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:05,800
Your adobo is so good.

119
00:07:05,933 --> 00:07:10,167
Thanks. Visit us more often.

120
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,167
King loves having you around.

121
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:17,100
But I'm sure he's not the only
one happy when you're around.

122
00:07:20,267 --> 00:07:27,133
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:36,900
[PHONE RINGING]

124
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:44,000
- [RINGING CONTINUES]
- [UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:47,067
Ma, excuse me a sec.

126
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,900
[RINGING CONTINUES]

127
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:50,133
Excuse me.

128
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:56,733
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:07:56,867 --> 00:07:58,400
Hello, sir?

130
00:07:58,533 --> 00:07:59,600
Samuel.

131
00:07:59,733 --> 00:08:03,433
We've got police assigned
to guard your family.

132
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:04,800
They're on their way now.

133
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:07,467
Okay, sir. Thank you.

134
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,533
You're welcome.

135
00:08:08,667 --> 00:08:12,967
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:16,200
Colonel said
security's arriving.

137
00:08:17,867 --> 00:08:19,567
That's good.

138
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,100
It means you're safe now.

139
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,167
I can probably go.

140
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:28,133
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

141
00:08:28,267 --> 00:08:29,133
- Okay.
- Mm.

142
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:37,300
Alright, I'll go now.

143
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:39,833
[LOLITA]
Yes, of course.

144
00:08:39,967 --> 00:08:43,000
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you. Thank you.

145
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:47,167
Bye, Aunt Agnes!
Come back, okay?

146
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:51,800
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

147
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:53,900
Of course, sweetie.

148
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:56,767
Be good.
We'll see each other again.

149
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:59,000
Maybe you should
walk Agnes out, Samuel

150
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:02,967
Unless you don't
want her to leave.

151
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:10,133
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:15,467
Okay. I'll go now.

153
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:22,067
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

154
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:24,200
Go upstairs and
brush your teeth.

155
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,300
Okay, Grandma.

156
00:09:25,433 --> 00:09:32,267
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

157
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:35,933
They're here.

158
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:43,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,433
That's Johnny's car.

160
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:49,467
What? Agnes?

161
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,233
[ENGINE REVVING]

162
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:52,333
Agnes.

163
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:55,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

164
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:57,267
Oh Agnes, did you
forget something?

165
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:00,767
Yes, I left something
in the bathroom.

166
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:07,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

167
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:11,000
Long time no see!

168
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,367
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

169
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,633
I heard you need
a security detail?

170
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:20,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:10:20,567 --> 00:10:22,300
At your service, Sir Scammer.

172
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:29,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

173
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:39,567
- Why you?
- Why not?

174
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:45,333
Who's the one saving you
from your father's victims?

175
00:10:45,467 --> 00:10:47,167
Isn't it me?

176
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:50,100
When your son was kidnapped,
who brought him back to you?

177
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,600
- Me.
- And because of that,

178
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:53,767
I owe you a lot.

179
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:56,733
But what you did for my family
is already enough,

180
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:58,033
you don't have
to watch over us.

181
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,633
Why, Trinidad?

182
00:10:59,767 --> 00:11:01,033
What is it--

183
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:03,333
are you afraid I'll find out
something about you?

184
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:07,467
What are you hiding?

185
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,967
Is this about your work
at Oriental Ridge?

186
00:11:12,233 --> 00:11:14,133
Are you in cahoots
with your bosses?

187
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:17,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:19,167
Is that why your son
was kidnapped...

189
00:11:20,133 --> 00:11:25,067
...and your boss's son was shot?

190
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:29,267
I don't know anything
about what you're saying.

191
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,300
Okay, fine.

192
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:32,167
We'll see.

193
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:34,033
If ever you want
to say something,

194
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:35,467
I'm just outside.

195
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,467
I'm security now.

196
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:43,467
So I'll watch over you.

197
00:11:43,633 --> 00:11:45,600
Okay?

198
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:47,500
I'll watch over you.

199
00:11:47,633 --> 00:11:54,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

200
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:08,100
- Samuel, what's the problem--
- Ma.

201
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:10,367
Hello. Do you remember me? +

202
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:13,067
I'm the one who saved
your grandson.

203
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,867
- Yes, the police officer.
- Just call me Johnny.

204
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:17,767
This is Noel, he's with me.

205
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:20,433
Hi, ma'am. Good evening.

206
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:21,867
Why are you here?

207
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,333
Is there another problem,
Samuel?

208
00:12:23,467 --> 00:12:24,667
[JOHNNY CHUCKLES]
She's funny.

209
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:28,433
No, ma'am, it's just that
I was assigned as your security.

210
00:12:28,567 --> 00:12:31,233
It's my hobby now
to protect you.

211
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:32,800
Perfect timing,
there's food inside.

212
00:12:32,933 --> 00:12:34,200
- Come in, come in--
- Ma.

213
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:35,500
- [JOHNNY] Sure!
- Ma!

214
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:36,633
I'm starving.

215
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:45,233
Come in.

216
00:12:45,367 --> 00:12:48,867
- I'll just prepare some food.
- Hey.

217
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:51,067
This house is huge.

218
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,833
It has rich people vibes.

219
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:54,067
Not bad.

220
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,733
[SAMUEL] Where are you?

221
00:12:57,867 --> 00:13:03,267
[PHONE VIBRATING]

222
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:09,133
[AGNES] In the bathroom.

223
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:11,800
Ma'am, can I use the bathroom,
is this the one?

224
00:13:11,933 --> 00:13:17,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:20,100
That's occupied.

226
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:25,067
[SAMUEL] Uh, upstairs
there's another bathroom.

227
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,300
Yes, upstairs, it's nicer.

228
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:34,467
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:38,267
- Noel, right?
- Yeah.

230
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:42,167
Come with me.
I'll show you the CCTV.

231
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:44,333
Might help you
while you're on watch.

232
00:13:52,167 --> 00:13:53,367
[LOLITA] So?

233
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:54,433
Success?

234
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:58,000
- Uh, yes, thank you again.
- That's good.

235
00:13:58,133 --> 00:14:00,267
- Alright then.
- Okay, take care.

236
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:07,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:17,967
Ma'am, your bathroom is amazing,

238
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:20,567
it flushes on its own.

239
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:21,600
So nice.

240
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:26,967
[PHONE VIBRATING]

241
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,933
[AGNES] I've already left.

242
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:31,800
Uh, come on, we can eat now.

243
00:14:31,933 --> 00:14:33,767
I'm fine, just coffee for me.

244
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:38,800
It's up to you.

245
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:40,233
This one looks expensive.

246
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:42,933
What is it?

247
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:47,900
Oh, an electric fan.

248
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:49,333
[CHUCKLES] Nice.

249
00:14:49,467 --> 00:14:54,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

250
00:15:04,267 --> 00:15:05,233
[EXHALES HEAVILY] Okay.

251
00:15:05,367 --> 00:15:06,300
Ah, Enzo!

252
00:15:06,433 --> 00:15:07,533
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:15:07,667 --> 00:15:08,900
Didn't expect  you to drop by.

254
00:15:09,833 --> 00:15:11,733
Hello, Miss Bekkah.
Is Papa inside?

255
00:15:11,867 --> 00:15:13,367
Oh no, he's currently
in a meeting.

256
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:15,367
But he should be done soon.

257
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,433
I'll wait for him inside.

258
00:15:16,567 --> 00:15:18,833
No, you can't go
into his office.

259
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:20,633
You know your father.

260
00:15:20,767 --> 00:15:22,000
He's very particular
about this stuff.

261
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:24,867
He doesn't want anyone
touching his belongings.

262
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:25,967
You know what?

263
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:28,167
How about you grab a few
snacks from the pantry?

264
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,467
- Um...
- Come on.

265
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,333
I'll just wait here,
Miss Bekkah.

266
00:15:31,467 --> 00:15:32,533
Are you sure?

267
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,267
- Yes.
- Okay.

268
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:44,767
[MUSIC BECOMES SUSPENSEFUL]

269
00:15:56,467 --> 00:15:57,467
[SECURITY GUARD] Sir!

270
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,833
That's currently out of order.

271
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:00,333
You can use the next elevator.

272
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:02,533
It's still out of order?

273
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:05,267
- They haven't fixed it yet?
- I'm afraid so.

274
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:09,267
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:16:09,433 --> 00:16:10,333
- Sir--
- Enzo!

276
00:16:11,167 --> 00:16:12,133
Pa.

277
00:16:12,267 --> 00:16:13,333
What's up?

278
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,933
It's still out of order, Pa.
Why not get someone to fix it?

279
00:16:21,433 --> 00:16:22,500
Come on, Pa.

280
00:16:22,633 --> 00:16:23,867
You have a beautiful
office space,

281
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,900
yet no money is being
spent on fixing the elevator.

282
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:28,833
Don't worry, once I've saved up
enough from my driving gig,

283
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:30,800
I'll help you out.

284
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:31,733
[SCOFFS]

285
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:36,733
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

286
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:39,933
Why do you care so much
about one broken elevator

287
00:16:40,067 --> 00:16:42,300
in my office?

288
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:44,933
Are you belittling me?

289
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,600
Looking down on my business?

290
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,367
How much do you earn
from your driving gig?

291
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,933
From your barista job?

292
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:51,867
- Tell me.
- Pa...

293
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:55,500
It was a joke.

294
00:16:55,633 --> 00:16:56,633
[ROLDAN INHALES DEEPLY]

295
00:16:56,767 --> 00:17:00,467
[MUSIC BECOMES DRAMATIC]

296
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,933
[SIGHS]

297
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:08,000
S-Sorry.

298
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:10,133
I'm way out of line.

299
00:17:11,767 --> 00:17:13,567
No matter how much we've argued,

300
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,367
I've never seen you
as anything less.

301
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:18,100
And I'll never scoff
at everything you've achieved

302
00:17:18,233 --> 00:17:19,267
in life.

303
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:26,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

304
00:17:28,533 --> 00:17:31,333
Why did you send Johnny?

305
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:34,700
He was referred to me by
my contact, a police chief.

306
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:35,967
They said he's decent.

307
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:37,967
A competent cop.

308
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:40,633
I had no idea
you two had any tension.

309
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:41,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

310
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,767
And he wanted this.

311
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,233
Policarpio volunteered
for the job.

312
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:47,933
He wanted to serve as a security
detail for your family.

313
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,067
He's been suspecting me
of being a scammer.

314
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:54,000
He doesn't give a damn
about my family's safety.

315
00:17:54,133 --> 00:17:56,167
He came here
to keep an eye on me.

316
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:57,167
[SIGHS]

317
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,267
Samuel.

318
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,500
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,467
I know Johnny can be
full of himself.

320
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:05,433
But I'm sure he'll do his best
for the job.

321
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:07,433
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

322
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:09,067
[EXHALES HEAVILY]
Think about it.

323
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:12,067
He's started asking around
about Oriental Ridge,

324
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:16,267
which suggests he wants to solve
King's kidnapping.

325
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:18,367
Samuel,

326
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,933
at this point,

327
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:24,067
since we're still unsure
who in the police force

328
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,100
might be
on the Riveras' payroll,

329
00:18:27,033 --> 00:18:29,367
Johnny is the only one
we can trust.

330
00:18:30,533 --> 00:18:33,733
I hope you're right, Agnes.

331
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:40,900
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

332
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:54,233
You really didn't have to come
all the way here, Auntie.

333
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,367
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

334
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:57,567
You know, I really owe you one.

335
00:18:57,700 --> 00:19:02,733
For helping my friends
who fell victims to the scam.

336
00:19:02,867 --> 00:19:04,100
Don't be silly now.

337
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:07,267
I much prefer the privacy here.

338
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,567
You know how it is
when it comes to legal matters.

339
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:12,200
You can't be too careful.
You never know who's listening.

340
00:19:12,333 --> 00:19:13,933
- [SOFTLY] Thank you, Auntie.
- [CHUCKLES]

341
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:15,433
I'll just serve the food.

342
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:17,967
I just have a few more questions

343
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:21,567
before filing claims
against the estate.

344
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:24,933
This way, at least a portion of
their money could be returned.

345
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:26,233
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,233
Hmm, okay.

347
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:29,133
So, Auntie, what exactly
do you need to know?

348
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:34,367
You're close with
Samuel Trinidad's family, right?

349
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:36,833
I'd say so, Auntie.

350
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:39,100
And you're aware that...

351
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:42,400
he's been implicated in the scam
orchestrated by his late father,

352
00:19:43,233 --> 00:19:45,933
which resulted in him losing
his job at Golden Trust Bank.

353
00:19:46,067 --> 00:19:49,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

354
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:50,933
Uh...

355
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:52,367
You know, Auntie...

356
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,067
I actually feel sorry for them.

357
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:57,767
During the peak of the public's
hatred toward them,

358
00:19:57,900 --> 00:20:00,300
they had to move
to a small apartment.

359
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:02,967
Then he even got stabbed.

360
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,000
[ENZO SIGHS DEEPLY]

361
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,667
But he is blacklisted
by every single company.

362
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

363
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,000
Except for
Oriental Ridge Estates.

364
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:17,900
[MUSIC BECOMES STIRRING]

365
00:20:18,033 --> 00:20:19,367
I want to hear your opinion.

366
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:24,133
Why do you think Samuel Trinidad
was hired by Jacob and Roldan?

367
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,333
Beats me, Auntie.

368
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:32,267
You know my father and I
don't talk much, right?

369
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,600
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

370
00:20:33,733 --> 00:20:35,533
And when we get
the chance to talk,

371
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:38,367
it almost always end up
in an argument.

372
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:41,833
Just like what happened
in the office.

373
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:43,333
What happened?

374
00:20:43,467 --> 00:20:44,667
Auntie...

375
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:46,433
I came to see him
at the office,

376
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:49,467
and while I was waiting,
I noticed the broken elevator.

377
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:50,867
That's it.

378
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,233
Oh, yeah. That one elevator.

379
00:20:54,367 --> 00:20:55,933
I made a joke about it,

380
00:20:56,067 --> 00:20:58,000
but he suddenly blew up at me.

381
00:20:59,067 --> 00:21:02,833
I don't think we'll ever be
on good terms.

382
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:04,533
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

383
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,100
[SIGHS]

384
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:07,367
Enzo.

385
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:10,333
I understand
your frustrations, okay?

386
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,233
But you have to remember

387
00:21:12,367 --> 00:21:14,133
he is still your father.

388
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:19,067
Running a company like that
isn't easy at all.

389
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,100
He was probably
just stressed out,

390
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:23,600
that's why he said all that.

391
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:27,300
But I'm pretty sure
he didn't mean it.

392
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:30,000
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

393
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:32,967
[LEAH] He snapped over
 a broken elevator?

394
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:36,700
A lot of things
don't add up, Jacob.

395
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:39,833
You and your brother Roldan
are keeping too many secrets.

396
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:41,733
From the very start,

397
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,733
you've always known
that I hate

398
00:21:44,867 --> 00:21:46,700
being kept in the dark, Jacob.

399
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:53,867
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

400
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:09,500
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

401
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:22,667
Make sure everything is
ready to go.

402
00:22:26,267 --> 00:22:27,900
In this very building,

403
00:22:29,533 --> 00:22:32,067
Trinidad will die
one way or another.

404
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,567
Do you understand?

405
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:41,400
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

406
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:49,267
This Wednesday...

407
00:22:49,433 --> 00:22:51,633
Scammers really do live large.

408
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:54,367
Don't you dare insult my son

409
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:56,267
in our own house ever again!

410
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:58,667
The sinners had
better be afraid.

411
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,433
Give this to King.

412
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:01,533
Be a good boy.

413
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:03,700
How about you meet my mom?

414
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,733
Check your email.

415
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:09,667
Roldan is the true mastermind
behind all the scams.

416
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,733
If you don't let me
into your group,

417
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:13,533
the whole world will see
that video.

418
00:23:13,667 --> 00:23:15,100
You have eight hours to decide.

419
00:23:15,233 --> 00:23:17,667
Sins of the Father.
